verbose_text: In contract, in the hES cells grown in a colony the differences depended on the location of the cells : at the centre, the RhoA-kinase controlled actin-myosin contraction was highly activated, while at the periphery the cells had a RhoA concentration gradient, were more prone to migrate and had higher internalisation of integrin beta1.
